@pevdh *maybe* the *WorkerThread* should catch all exceptions generated by the *task* and log it with level *ERROR* telling about the exception name and details. This will avoid the WorkerThread dying.

For example ApiExceptions may occur when bot kicked from a group immediately after one user use a command and the bot tries to reply, and it's kinda annoying because people is not aware this could happen.

Other source of Exceptions is, for example, file manipulation (don't exist, no permissions, etc...) but this kind of exceptions SHOULD be catch by the users but if its not this kills the WorkerThread (yep I did a quick'n'dirty bot code that had this problem xD).

