@voisine >*Does Japanese have a standard alphabetical order?*

No idea. I'm just going by what is said in the [StackOverflow post of mine](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/31156424/binary-search-bisect-for-a-unicode-character-in-python-2-7) as the `binary_search` function is part of [this repository's source code](https://github.com/trezor/python-mnemonic/blob/master/mnemonic/mnemonic.py#L38-L42), afterall, so as the [SO response notes](http://stackoverflow.com/a/31156743/3936486), **binary search functions require _sorted_ word lists**. As such, [Japanese BIP39 test vectors fail](https://github.com/bip32JP/bip32JP.github.io/blob/master/test_JP_BIP39.json) for *some* of the vectors if `binary_search` is used. 

As you say the wordlist order is cumbersome to change; therefore the binary_search function must be deprecated in favour of a traditional (and slower) `list.index`

OK, I see the rationale, but instead of entirely separate test methods, could we just switch on the Python version *inside* the method?

```python
def test_convert_volume_binds_unicode_bytes_input(self):
    if six.PY2:
        expected = [unicode('/mnt/지연:/unicode/박:rw', 'utf-8')]
        data = {
            '/mnt/지연': {
                'bind': '/unicode/박',
                'mode': 'rw'
            }
        }
    else:
        expected = ['/mnt/지연:/unicode/박:rw']
        data = {
            bytes('/mnt/지연', 'utf-8'): {
                'bind': bytes('/unicode/박', 'utf-8'),
                'mode': 'rw'
            }
        }

    self.assertEqual(convert_volume_binds(data), expected)

def test_convert_volume_binds_unicode_unicode_input(self):
    if six.PY2:
        expected = [unicode('/mnt/지연:/unicode/박:rw', 'utf-8')]
        data = {
            unicode('/mnt/지연', 'utf-8'): {
                'bind': unicode('/unicode/박', 'utf-8'),
                'mode': 'rw'
            }
        }
    else:
        expected = ['/mnt/지연:/unicode/박:rw']
        data = {
            '/mnt/지연': {
                'bind': '/unicode/박',
                'mode': 'rw'
            }
        }

    self.assertEqual(convert_volume_binds(data), expected)
```

